Mohammed delivered the keynote address at Madikizela-Mandela's memorial in Harlem, New York, last night.  

In a tribute at the historic Abyssinian Baptist Church, Mam Winnie's life was commemorated with stories of her trials and triumphs, reflections on her resilience in the face of the apartheid machine and the impact her legacy will continue to have despite her physical departure. Sherwin Bryce-Pease reports… --SABC--